# 📊 Data Analytics L1 - Exploratory Data Analysis on Retail Sales Data

## 📌 Project Overview
This project focuses on performing Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a retail sales dataset to uncover valuable business insights. Python was used for data cleaning, preprocessing, visualization, and statistical analysis to understand customer purchasing behavior and sales trends.

## 🎯 Objectives
- Clean and preprocess the retail sales dataset.
- Perform exploratory data analysis.
- Identify sales trends and customer behavior.
- Visualize important business insights.
- Generate meaningful conclusions from the data.

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

## 📂 Dataset
The dataset contains retail sales information such as:
- Customer ID
- Gender
- Age
- Product Category
- Quantity
- Price per Unit
- Total Amount
- Date

## 📊 Analysis Performed
- Data Cleaning
- Missing Value Check
- Duplicate Removal
- Descriptive Statistics
- Correlation Analysis
- Sales Distribution
- Product Category Analysis
- Customer Age Distribution
- Gender-wise Analysis
- Monthly Sales Trend
- Data Visualization

## 📈 Visualizations
- Histogram
- Box Plot
- Count Plot
- Correlation Heatmap
- Bar Chart
- Line Chart

## 📌 Key Insights
- Identified the most purchased product categories.
- Analyzed customer demographics.
- Observed sales trends over time.
- Found relationships between numerical variables.
- Generated business insights using data visualization.

